+++ Mantle Cinder Aqua Rubble Mist Cyndro Truttle +++

Cinder and Mist walked down one of the hallways of Maximal city. They
were both dwelling on their own thoughts to an extent. Mantle, Aqua,
and Rubble were in the holo-rooms training with the rest of the
Maximals.
"So did you get to talk to him?" Mist asked her 'daughter' when they
stopped near a console to check on the status of the city. Cinder
shook her head a bit sadly.

"No. They went straight to training." She said and tapped a few keys.
They stood there in silence, and then Cinder got bored with all the
info that the computer was telling her and the two women walkeed on.
"I wish they could get some rest though. I don't know about them, but
I'd get bored always fighting."

Mist nodded in reply, and her and Cinder heard voices up ahead near
the exit to the city. They sped up and headed toward them.



Cyndro had taken care of all the rest of the configuration from the
extra parts that were added to the Element from the Cybertronian Fire
to make Maximal City. His nanobots were cleaning up the field where
the old ship used to be, and there was barely any trace of it
anymore. The ground was being smoothed over and blast marks and scrap
metal were being removed. The nanobots carried in new grass molecule
by molecule and there was now new greenery growing around the city.
The solar panels were sunning themselves successfully, and Cyndro
could feel his power rising to full after the battle.

Checking the scanners, Cyndro realized that he had missed the fact
that several bots were standing outside the city. He made a mental
note not to slip up like that again, and then proceeded to meet them.

The large entrance hatch to Maximal City opened and a screen detached
from the cealing, carried by a few metalling beams out of the city.
On the screen was a boyish bot's face, smiling at all the bots
around. He counted ten in all.

"Hello, everyone," he said with a friendly tone, "I'm sorry to keep
you waiting, but getting a city set up is a bit hard."

He then looked around, and the screen turned so that he could look at
everyone through the cameras on its corners. "I'm Cyndro. The city's
mind. Its nice to meet you.
